fields.title: {"en": "Pre-test"}
{"en": "Match the phrases with the corresponding words."}
{"en": "Match the following phrases with the corresponding words below."}
{"en": "Match the definitions with the corresponding words below."}
{"en": "Match the type of waste to its category"}
{"en": "Match the sources of waste with the types of solid waste below."}
{"en": "Water-washed diseases are caused by drinking water that has been contaminated with pathogens."}
{"en": "Diarrhoea and typhoid fever are diseases that occur when water is scarce."}
{"en": "Children may become infected with bilharzia if they swim and play in lakes where there are many snails."}
{"en": "Malaria is an example of a waterborne disease."}
{"en": "Community empowerment has no input in provision of safe water."}
{"en": "New technologies can help to overcome the barriers to the provision of safe water."}
{"en": "Local government should not be involved in finding sustainable solutions for provision of safe water."}
{"en": "Provision of safe water improves the lives of infants and children."}
{"en": "E.coli is a type of virus found in faeces."}
{"en": "Faecal coliforms are typically found in human and animal faeces."}
{"en": "The presence of E.coli in a water sample means the water is safe to drink."}
{"en": "The absence of E.coli in a water sample means the water is safe to drink."}
{"en": "The decomposition of human waste in a septic tank is an aerobic process."}
{"en": "A seepage pit is a watertight underground pit for containing liquid waste."}
{"en": "Anaerobic digestion is a method of waste treatment that converts waste into useful products."}
{"en": "Runoff does not cause environmental problems because it is only rainwater that runs off the land surface."}
{"en": "Protection of groundwater from contamination is an essential requirement of human waste management."}
{"en": "Recycling is the best approach to solid waste management."}
{"en": "Composting is an aerobic decomposition process for converting organic solid waste into useful compost."}
{"en": "Reusing plastic water bottles is an example of waste recovery."}
{"en": "Controlled tipping is so called because only a limited quantity of waste can be tipped at any one time."}
{"en": "Healthcare waste contains hazardous and non-hazardous waste."}
{"en": "Infectious healthcare waste is kept in red containers."}
{"en": "Chemical disinfection involves treating waste with 0.5% chlorine solution for 10 minutes by immersing in an autoclave."}
